The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter A BULAWAYO businessman and private investigator who exposed former head of the Roman Catholic Church in Bulawayo, Archbishop Pius Ncube’s sexual escapades in 2007, Earnest Tekere has died. <img class="alignnone wp-image-550672 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  Tekere, managing director of Home Guard Security Services, a Bulawayo-based private investigations company, allegedly committed suicide by hanging him at his offices situated at Josiah Tongogara and 13th Avenue in the city centre shortly before 3PM. <img class="alignnone wp-image-550669 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Pias-picture-f2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  When a Chronicle news crew visited the scene shortly after the incident, relatives had gathered outside the Home Guard Security Services premises. Police were also at the scene ready to collect the body. …more to follow